						               													<description>Updated and Replaced by &amp;quot;Zulu Skirmish&amp;quot; in December 2020 - Click the &amp;quot;Zulu Skirmish&amp;quot; re-implemented link in header.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Zulu Rules for Miniatures is a Regimental level table Top Game that plays like a Skirmish Game.  Use your own 28mm-15mm figures.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Zulu teaches you how to structure your British, Boers and Zulus.  It walks you through all games steps by providing you with over 45 pictures and illustrations that will assist you in learning how to build, mount and play your Zulu, Boer or British Armies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Zulu also includes one page of Tokens and 51 &amp;ldquo;Copy and Cut&amp;rdquo;  and Cards for Leaders and Units.  You can cut them out, fold them in half and slip them into sleeves from your local game store, or simply glue stick them together on card stock.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You will also need a handful of d6 and 10 each d10 dice per Army, a measuring stick and period miniatures to play the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
